Mulkosaur Rex Archmage <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=briljin>Briljin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#333333>(12/16/02 2:18:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=417.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: To Balance damage dealers within the game, my view.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>All of the second string damage classes should have a significant contribution here, with the probable exception of monks</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
My question is did you take into account the way PoP affected classes within this area?  For example, Necromancer.  We lost alot of the secondary utility that we once possed before PoP due to lack of upgrades, level limitations upon spells and the intensity of mobs in PoP.<br>
<br>
The days of Necromancers using ST (necro mez) as CC or acting as a healing (pact line) are over in PoP.  The level cap upon ST is too low for PoP and mobs hit in one attack for more damage then I can heal in 24 seconds.<br>
<br>
Our ability to debuff the mob is well below that of either of the real debuffing classes (Shamans, Chanters) and our ability to lower resistance is limited to Fire, Poison and Disease and is below that which Mages and Shaman can low all resists (but disease for Mages).<br>
<br>
What utility I do have left can generally be replaced by just about any other class.  Shamans and Chanters can slow better.  Chanters can CC or charm better.  All healers, and in some situations even Hybrid melees, are vastly superior healers.<br>
<br>
In PoP I am not sought after for my utility abilities, instead I have become one that can sustain pretty high damage output.  With a Rogue pet, Toxin, Lich and a some fast acting DoTs I have become a very good sustained damage dealer.<br>
<br>
Plus I think your bulking types of damage up into one category and neglecting that there are different types of damage.  Wizards have always been strong as &quot;burst&quot; types of damage, while weak at sustained damage.  Necromancers have been weak at &quot;burst&quot; damage but much stronger at sustained damage.<br>
<br>
Bril <br>
<br>
