 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=briljin>Briljin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/16/02 2:19:23 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=necridious>Necridious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 148<br> <font color=#333333>(12/16/02 6:51:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=417.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: To Balance damage dealers within the game, my view.</span><hr size=1> Briljin, I feel for the necromancers, my original main was a necromancer too, and I got tired of soloing all the time, so I started a Wizard. /rofl....   <br>
<br>
I have reams of ideas about Necromancers, and where they should stand on that ladder.  I originally put them in with crowd controllers, but I realize that for that to happen, tons of upgrades would need to be implemented.  In the original document I wrote these up in, I had alot of notes about changes to necromancers to make them fit a Damage/utility role much better than they do, but I took them back out as my intention was to address my thoughts on the heavy hitters, not necromancers.<br>
<br>
1. I feel that the spells Boon of the Garou and the new Scarecrow illusion are clearly necromancer themed spells, and should be at least shared, if not unique to the necromancer class.<br>
<br>
2. I feel that the Necromancer should rate as a viable back up healer.  Coral Empathy should have it's mana cost reduced to no more than 15 to be in line with the other Necromancer healing spells, and that upgrades that do up to 1000 points of transfer should be available for instant healing, and large heal-over-time spells that require the use of the lifetap drains to survive should exist.<br>
<br>
3. I believe that the Screaming Terror line of spells should be expanded into a full mez line of spells based on fear.  I believe it should effect mobs that are immune to mez, but be useless against mobs that are immune to fear-- with appropriate re-tuneing of some zones so that this would make sence.  This would create a choice based on situation on who you want doing your crowd control.<br>
<br>
4. I believe that at the very least, a series of Lifetap Proc buffs should be implemented for Necromancers to cast on their groupmates, it's sick that enchanters can do this and necromancers cannot.  I further believe that spells like Mark of Karn, and Mark of Retribution fall squarely within the Necromancers concept, and should be at least shared, if not unique to the necromancer.  Lastly, why  are Necromancers the only Int caster with self-only damage sheilds--while Banshee aura and any possible upgrades should not challenge Mage or Druid DS, it should be an option for those groups without another DS caster.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>As an end note on my views of the balance of damage output. Necromancers should probably replace Wizards or Mages on some fights in the ranks of the heavy hitters, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>especially those fights that last a long time</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, or where Fire/Magic resist is high, and Disease/Poison is not.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I didnt forget about the different types of damage Burst /vs Sustained, I just dont feel that necromancers need to be on the top rung, unless the mob has exceptionally high hitpoints, with decent pet hittable AC so that the necromancer strengths, like the rogue strengths are highlighted.  With lower DPS pets, Necromancers should not be matching a mage in a heavy damaging catagory like this, unless mana becomes an issue like them 1 million hp mobs in vellious.  <br>
<br>
It's my view that the strength of the Necromancer class is it's flexability, similar to the Druid class in that respect.  The difference is that while druids were able to help a group, necromancers got nothing till Luclin that we could share in an otherwise social game.  Many of the spells we got before level 20 would have been great for a melee, but they were never upgraded and are useless once a Necromancer stops meleeing.  I am sure the Shadowknights enjoyed the self only DS, lifetaps, Lifetap proc buff, and melee debuff dots, but of those, only the dots were of assistance to a group, and people see them as slow damage, not a debuff.<br>
<br>
<br>
As to soloing--I can't help that Rogues can't solo, but in no way should that mean that they need to completely outdamage everyone all of the time.  Being able to solo is an effect of a simple game mechanic--be able to do significant damage to the enemy while taking minimal damage to yourself.  This is what casters are all about- tremendous damage at range.  Rogues are tremendous melee damage, and they made that choice at character creation.  Possibly the only thing that could help them solo would be if poisons for snare and fear were implemented, or one that allowed them to proc a long lasting stun--but if you can solo melee a mob solo without taking damage, something is dreadfully wrong.  A second way to balance this factor would be to make caster mobs weak in melee and strong on range damage, then a rogue that could theoreticaly keep the mob from casting could solo it, but this would require game and AI changes that would be alot of work.  As such, it's probably not going to happen.  For a look at good AI on ranged mobs, look at Blizzard games-- get close to an archer or caster, and they will try to fight for a few seconds at close range, maybe, but then they try to get some distance before resuming their ranged attacks, which are as powerfull if not more so than any melee attack.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Why not just put in &quot;Summon: Vex Thall Key&quot; and throw it on a vendor for 25pp?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Now here's a statement that was un-called for.  <br>
<br>
Perhaps this was in reference to the summon pet only Seru/Shissar bane weapons.  How would this instantly get everyone into Vex-Thall?  If the quest is as hard as getting the weapons themselves, and only usable by pets, most guilds arn't going to bother with it... and certainly it's not going to short circut the Emp and Seru kills in such a way as to allow one mage to do get this spell and jump his guild through massive pet zerging to Vex Thall.  If it's reference to actual usefull summons that people will want....<br>
<br>
If you feel that any summons that a mage gets except for pets should be trivial junk not worth the time it takes to memorize, I'd guess that is a valid oppinion, though it wouldn't be mine.  With the resist changes recently, it's hard, unless you have extremely good gear, to get your resists to a point where you can reliably resist mob spells, and your casters should be able to help with this--VI feels the same, elsewise every other casting class would not get spells to enhance resists.  I've always felt that the weapon summons should have been upgraded with the expansions to match the new ratio's of weapons that drop commonly, and I find it tragic that mages summon armor for every class but their own by level 40.  I feel that cloth armor with caster usefull effects like flowing thought would make up for the personal mana regen lost by the t-rod nerf, would benefit all by stacking with Clarity, the Spiritual line, and bards, and it's the rare very rare caster with higher than FT8--there's the boots and Shawl for 6?  I'm sure your above average guys could sqeeze another 2 from somewhere.  I also find it silly that a Post 50 summoner looks foward to finally conjuring Beer.  Store bought items are fine for low level summons, but the high ones should be special and unique to the mage class-- as in something people are actually going to ask for.  As I said, the days of the only usefull mage summonings being coldstone, Ring of Flight, and Waterstone should have died in Kunark.<br>
