 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojirax.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nanamarinfernostorm>Nanamar Infernostorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 612<br> <font color=#333333>(12/17/02 5:50:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=417.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: To Balance damage dealers within the game, my view.</span><hr size=1> Well, necros conststently do 100+ DPS, thats not bad, putting rangers out of the top rung is just ignorance, Rangers can consistently outdamage me and TS = me chain nuking w/ a bigger mana pool than I have... <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=386526" target="top">Master Nanamar Infernostorm</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Tunare's Arch Mage of the 65th Summoning<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.bloodofhonor.waxscript.com/" target="top">Blood of Honor</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Fennin Ro<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=necridious>Necridious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#333333>(12/17/02 6:45:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=417.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.atl.bellsouth.net/atl/d/a/dastorys/Pictures/Nec-60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: To Balance damage dealers within the game, my view.</span><hr size=1> The only problem with what rangers is doing is that it's nearly aggro free, and with endless quiver costs nothing.<br>
<br>
<br>
I have no problem at all with archery being casting class damage, so long as they suffer similar penalties.  Rangers do suffer low hitpoints, though not as low as ours.  They do suffer from lack of AC, though not as low as ours.  If not for Endless Quiver, those 14 damage arrows would be pretty dang limited in supply.<br>
<br>
To do the damage that outdamages high level casters with all of their spells however takes a High End bow, High End fletched arrows, and at least archery mastery.  Endless quiver helps greatly as they don't burn up the arrows required to sustain this damage---but this is the flaw in that setup.  If they had to pay the pp for the arrows, and used them up, it would be a whole new ball game, and a trick reserved for big fights and Wowing the crowd.<br>
<br>
<br>
And Bril, back to Necro talk.<br>
<br>
Necromancers, nor any pet class, have ever had a problem with sustaining damage output.  The difficulty lies in sustaining an exceptional damage output.  If you look at my second string/utility classes, they all excell at putting out good damage over any length of time you care to measure.  In the case of the necromancer, due to the efficency and high damage of dots over long periods of time on one target, they actually start to eclipse those classes that do Large damage.  Of course, this ability is negated in most fights that don't last longer than 2 minutes.<br>
<br>
Due to the Flexability of Necromancers other abilities, I don't believe they should be on that top rung all the time.  I do believe that their utility abilities need to be brought back into line, and expanded a significant amount to make them group friendly at all levels, in a variety of situations.  I see the cornerstone of that utility being crowd control, if only they would expand what they have already given necromancers to be more universally usable.  Back up healing is also powerfull, though with the way a Necromancer's spells work, too dangerous in hazardous areas to use to the degree I propose.<br>
<br>
And I'm sorry, but classes must be grouped in some way.  There are only 6 spots in a group.  There are 15 classes.  Each class has a primary ability, and it needs to be a group function, which means some grouping must occur.  I choose to do this in 5 main catagories, as it's easiest to divide the classes evenly that way, and BuffBot isn't something I want anyone to have to do ALL the time.  Nearly all classes have some fall back ability they can use, for many buffs is it.  The only class I have a really hard time putting somewhere is monks.  If I it Truely was up to me to design the classes, rogues would drop to that Secondary Damage area, and Monks would move up, but that would assume there are many locked doors, traps, and need for pickpockets in the game world-- as in the utility they have would be meaningful.  So, until 15 man grouping is implemented in game with content to match, I'm afraid we are all going to have to fit into a 6 slot box.  Wanting Rogues to wear silk and have Fewer HP would be kinda like saying casters can wear chain, have a few hundred extra HP, but have to be in melee range to cast...have fun with that.<br>
<br>
Nothing I have suggested is wholesale revamping of EQ.  Somethings, like Rogue skills and some bard songs, have been broken since release, either through poor implementation, design, or coding. Other things just never scaled with the expansions, like caster spells, for instance, mage summons.  Somethings, until recently didn't scale with levels in proportion to others with the same jobs, like the Healers.  All I propose is a simple scheme of where each class belongs in an average, functioning xp group, and such changes as to make them good choices for that spot, as well as making the back up option also attractive to a group.  Done correctly, this will translate to raids, as a raid need the same basic things a group needs, only to a much greater degree.  So long as the back up abilities are varied and usefull, all will have a role when it comes time to squish the big winged lizard of choice. <p><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=448514">Antrygus Windrose </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=briljin>Briljin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#333333>(12/17/02 2:24:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=417.topic&index=15>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: To Balance damage dealers within the game, my view.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Do you like being the hi damage dealer now?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Myself, I love it and so do most the Necromancers I know but then I am in a primary raiding guild.  I would much rather be a steady high sustained damage dealer then a third rate utility class.  There just is not call for such a class, espically in PoP.  You are not really going to do much without a serious healer or Mez'ing class.<br>
<br>
The change is kind of like what Mages have gone thru.  SoE steped up the temp of the game with PoP, along with some classes that were starting to fall behind.  We lose some utility and some solo options but in return we gained alot of damage output in groups.  <br>
<br>
Lets face it, unless SoE was willing to upgrade Necromancer healing to near Druid/Shaman level and seriously improve our mez ability (heck, we only had ONE mez spell to begin with...) then that utility was going to become extinct anyways.  It was already starting to towards the later end of Luclin.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>- Let the stat taps hit pets too.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Actually I wish all group and AE buffs worked upon pets.  They are after all affected by all adverse AE attacks, so it is only fair that pets should get the benefit of AE buffs aswell.  SoE once mentioned that they were looking into this but it appears to have fallen to the side.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Let's not fall prey to the illusion that VI is listening and cares.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I think that is a pretty closeminded opinion.  SoE has made some very drastic changes to the game based purily upon player input.  Considering they continue to claim that EQ I will remain as long as there is a player base for it and the rumors of yet another expansion, I am pretty sure that SoE is listening they just may not answer or not give an answer you wish to hear.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Necromancers, nor any pet class, have ever had a problem with sustaining damage output.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Your forgetting that Necromancers until very recently had very weak DD ability (below that of Chanters and Clerics) and your average group made DoTs mana ineffectient because they would hardly reach their full duration.    <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Of course, this ability is negated in most fights that don't last longer than 2 minutes.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Correct. Unless the fight was long enough to allow for DoT stacking, DD has always been a better means of damage.  A lack of DD has always been a weakness in the Necromancer class until recently.  Not to mention the imbalanced power between DD and DoTs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Due to the Flexability of Necromancers other abilities, I don't believe they should be on that top rung all the time.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I am not saying they belong in your top rung either, what I am saying is you can not group classes like that because they excel at different types of damage.  A Wizard excels at burst damage but are pretty weak are sustained damage.  <br>
<br>
Your attempting to draw parallels that can not be made.  Wizards should be the undisputed masters of quick damage but not the masters of all types of damage.  Your trying to mix types into one category.<br>
<br>
Bril<br>
<br>
<br>
