<br>
Perhaps you want to go back to LFG for hours because the group wants a rogue for damage, but I certainly don't.  I never got a group based on being able to stun, once for evac, never for snare, never for Teleports and never because I could drop a few K damage in a few seconds.  I don't recall ever having invited a Mage into a group based on his 'leet summonses either.  In both cases, just as with the rogue, We were invited for damage.  In the days when there was only one true Damage King, the prince need not apply for pick-up groups, except in uncommon situations--especially right after kunark was released and everyone+their brother made rogue twinks, at least those not working on their Iksar Monks.  Vellious and the billion HP mobs didn't help much either.  I suggest you go back and read some of the old threads on this very board discussing those issues back then.<br>
<br>
Hobie wan, I'm with you.  There's nothing inherently wrong with the improved ranger damage, certainly I have no problem with it's performance under the Trueshot dicipline, as that is an extremly limited use.  My single problem is with the effect of endless quiver combined with High end archery--making it nearly aggro free, cost free damage.  With Spellcasting Mastery and full Specialization, that's what? 20% mana savings?  I'd be fine if endless quiver had a 20% chance to not use the arrow.  Those High End arrows are expensive to produce, take a high fletching skill and hunted components.  If they had to constantly replenish this supply, that would be fine. <p><br>
